    public class BaseFixture
extends java.lang.Object
    BaseFixture class contains functions which run before starting test and after test finishes execution. Before starting test, Appium Driver is launched on device and after test finishes Appium session is closed on device. On test case start , application under test is launched on device and credentials are passed for user to login. On test case finish, user is logged out of application and application under test is closed, so that each test launches independent of other tests. Configuration data like deviceName,platformName,Activity name, Package name etc is fetched from properties and testng.xml It also contains methods to check if Appium service is running,if Appium installed from CLI mode. Also contains functions to seed/flush images from android device.
    Author:
    Jaspreet Kaur Chagger, Sivaprakash Selvaraj

      • beforeTest

        @BeforeTest
public void beforeTest(java.lang.String emulator,
                                    java.lang.String platformName,
                                    java.lang.String platformVersion,
                                    java.lang.String deviceName,
                                    java.lang.String systemPort,
                                    java.lang.String chromeDriverPort,
                                    java.lang.String wdaLocalPort,
                                    java.lang.String webkitDebugProxyPort,
                                    java.lang.String screenshotCaptureStage,
                                    java.lang.String passScreenshotFlag,
                                    org.testng.ITestContext context)
                             throws java.lang.Exception
        Launches AppiumDriver on mobile device. This method will be executed first before any test. Parameters passed in this method are passed from testng.xml
        Parameters:
        emulator - true if device is emulator (Optional parameter,Android Only, Values: true/false)
        platformName - Platform Name (Values: Android/iOS)
        platformVersion - Platform Version
        deviceName - Device name
        systemPort - unique system port for each parallel session (Optional parameter,Android Only)
        chromeDriverPort - the chromedriver port (if using webviews or chrome) (Optional parameter,Android Only)
        wdaLocalPort - unique system port for each parallel session (Optional parameter,iOS Only)
        webkitDebugProxyPort - port for accessing web views on real iOS device (Optional parameter,iOS Only)
        screenshotCaptureStage - screenshotCaptureStage controls the screenshot functionality of the testing, “1” for Taking screenshot at Test Step level and “2” for taking screenshot at test case level.
        passScreenshotFlag - If screenshots are required for Passed testcases, set it to "Y"
        context - ITestContext
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - throws all exception
